# ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Broker Research Dashboard — runtime env
# Copy to .env.local and tune per environment. Vite picks up VITE_* only.
#
# The dashboard is a read-only analytics client. It does NOT ingest mail,
# authenticate users, or enforce tenant isolation — all three live in the
# external upstream API. See docs/architecture.md.
# ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# ── PRIMARY: live forwarded-email feed (GET /email/forwarded) ────────────
# The dashboard's real data source. When VITE_BACKEND_API_URL is set, the app
# fetches the feed live at boot — paginated, deduped, newest-first — and renders
# against it (see src/app/previewBootstrap.ts). Auth is direct browser→backend:
# the bearer token comes from the host scope bootstrap, falling back to
# VITE_API_TOKEN below. No trailing slash.
#   VITE_BACKEND_API_URL=https://<munshot-backend>
# On Cloudflare Pages, set VITE_BACKEND_API_URL + VITE_API_TOKEN as build env
# vars so the live deploy renders real data.
VITE_BACKEND_API_URL=

# In-app Mock⇄Live toggle: a header button flips the whole dashboard between the
# live feed and the curated mock ("how it should look") for side-by-side
# comparison. Runtime control, no env var. Remove it (and src/mocks) once the
# live feed reaches parity.

# Which adapter backs the UI.
#
#   upstream   Production path. HttpResearchAdapter hits the external upstream
#              API. Scope (org, user) comes from the bearer token the host
#              injects via window.__BROKER_RESEARCH_DASHBOARD__ (see
#              docs/scope.md). This dashboard does not mint tokens.
#
#   local      Local dev harness. Same HTTP contract as `upstream`, but pointed
#              at the local server/ process which parses .eml fixtures from
#              server/fixtures/. Not a production path; handy for iterating on
#              the adapter, parsers, and UI without an upstream.
#
#   mock       Offline default. MockResearchAdapter serves src/mocks/* directly
#              and runs the deterministic engine on demand. No network.
#
#   mock-http  HttpResearchAdapter wired to a stub fetch backed by the mock
#              adapter. Exercises the full HTTP code path without a server —
#              the right mode for adapter-layer regression tests.
#
#   upstream-fixture
#              FixtureUpstreamAdapter. Serves the JSON fixtures in
#              src/adapters/upstream/fixtures/ through the translation
#              layer. Integration-rehearsal mode — use this to exercise the
#              wire-shape handshake offline before the real upstream ships.
#
# Leave UNSET for the default `server` adapter — the live forwarded-email feed
# path above. Only set this for dev/test harnesses (see docs/modes.md). The
# curated mock is reachable at runtime via the in-app Mock⇄Live toggle, so you
# no longer need `mock` mode just to see it.
# VITE_RESEARCH_ADAPTER=

# Base URL the HTTP adapter prefixes to every request. Required when
# VITE_RESEARCH_ADAPTER=upstream or =local. No trailing slash.
#   VITE_API_BASE_URL=https://api.broker-research.example.com
VITE_API_BASE_URL=

# Bearer token for the live feed (direct browser→backend auth — the chosen
# auth model for this build). The app reads the host scope bootstrap first
# (window.__BROKER_RESEARCH_DASHBOARD__.token) and falls back to this. For the
# standalone live deploy, set this (and VITE_BACKEND_API_URL) as a Cloudflare
# Pages build env var.
# ⚠ This token is inlined into the client bundle at build time and will expire —
#   rotate it, or move to a token-injecting proxy, before any wide release.
VITE_API_TOKEN=

# Raw-upstream → /v1 normalization profile. Applied at the HTTP boundary
# before the /v1 mappers see a response.
#
#   identity           (default) upstream already speaks /v1
#   example | example-divergent
#                      the bundled demonstration profile (envelope +
#                      snake_case + alt-ID + partial pagination)
#
# For a real vendor profile, inject the full object via
# window.__BROKER_RESEARCH_DASHBOARD__.normalizationProfile. See
# docs/upstream-normalization-bridge.md.
VITE_UPSTREAM_PROFILE=identity

# Live CMP (Current Market Price) endpoint override.
#
# Leave blank in production — the dashboard calls the same-origin Cloudflare
# Pages Function at `/api/stock-price`, which proxies the upstream quote API
# with edge caching (see functions/api/stock-price.ts).
#
# Set during local dev when running plain `npm run dev` (no Pages Function
# locally), e.g. to a deployed preview branch URL so the GET→POST translation
# and edge cache still work end-to-end:
#   VITE_STOCK_PRICE_URL=https://<preview>.broker-research-dashboard.pages.dev/api/stock-price
#
# For full-fidelity local testing (function + cache running locally) use
# `npm run dev:pages` instead, which runs wrangler against ./functions.
VITE_STOCK_PRICE_URL=

# Local-only fallback for the Live side: when set (and VITE_BACKEND_API_URL is
# NOT), the app loads the bundled sample /email/forwarded response at boot so the
# dashboard shows realistic data before the real backend is wired. Leave unset in
# production. A real VITE_BACKEND_API_URL always takes precedence over this.
# VITE_PREVIEW_FIXTURE=1
